AeroScan v0.2b
NEW: The GUI now starts automatically at boot
(drop to a shell with: systemctl stop
aeroscan-gui). Map Scope aircraft now match
Radar Scope — arrow icon with callsign and
altitude labels at the icon's 5 o'clock, 2/3
size. The GPS rail slot shows velocity (kt)
and altitude (ft) in fix-status colors. Radio
tuner: a missing-FAA-database notice now leads
the preset list (download via Settings > Radio
Options > Update Radio Data); new Parhelia
background watermark.

FINDINGS: the DSI display panel jams ADS-B
reception. Greatly improve it by remoting the
SDR stick on a USB extension cable and
experimenting with antenna placement — watch
the SDR rail's NF meter: -42 quiet, -30 jammed.
